rows.title: Spirit wars Native North American religions in the age of nation building Ronald Niezen ; with contributions by Manley Begay, Jr. [and others]

notes.label: Notes
notes.content: NMAI copy 39088009290503 has bookplate: Smithsonian Institution Libraries, Gift of Mrs. Ruth Webb.

notes.label: Contents
notes.content: Introduction -- The conquest of souls -- Learning to forget -- Medical evangelism -- The politics of repression -- The collectors -- Apostles of the new age -- Conclusions

notes.label: Summary
notes.content: Spirit Wars is an exploration of the ways in which the destruction of spiritual practices and beliefs of native peoples in North America has led to conditions of collective suffering--a process sometimes referred to as cultural genocide. Ronald Niezen approaches this topic through wide-ranging case studies involving different colonial powers and state governments: the seventeenth-century Spanish occupation of the Southwest, the colonization of the Northeast by the French and British, nineteenth-century westward expansion and nationalism in the swelling United States and Canada, and twentieth-century struggles for native people's spiritual integrity and freedom. Each chapter deals with a specific dimension of the relationship between native peoples and non-native institutions, and together these topics yield a new understanding of the forces directed against the underpinnings of native cultures

notes.content: A DNA extraction was processed for this tissue, but based on the resulting COI sequence it was determined that a subsampling offset error occurred. The DNA extraction was discarded, but the tissue retained. It is unclear whether the sampling error occurred in the field, thus affecting archival tissue, or if the error was restricted to secondary sampling for the digestion plates, limiting the problem to the DNA extract. Follow-up analysis on tissues from MARQ-221 through MARQ-262 has yet to be conducted, so potential users should be informed of the issue prior to distribution of tissue aliquots from this range.
